title: Onyshko helps Canada sit 5th after opening day
text:
Onyshko helps Canada sit 5th after opening day By: Uncredited Report Error 
Team Canada, including Brandon’s Isabela Onyshko, sat fifth overall as 12 of the 24 countries at the World Artistic Gymnastics Championships completed their qualifying on Friday in Glasglow, Scotland. 
The top eight teams qualify for the 2016 Rio Olympics, while the next eight earn a berth in a last-chance event, where four more spots will be available. 
Onyshko is eighth of 118 gymnasts on the uneven bars with a score of 14.100, 22nd of 120 in floor exercises (13.700), 29th of 118 in balance beam (13.416) and 17th of 97 all-around (55.216). 
Canada’s Ellie Black was first all-around, sixth in vault, first in beam and eighth in floor, with the other 12 teams set to qualify early Saturday. 
Russia, Germany, Italy and Japan were ahead of Canada after the first day. 
The women’s finals take place on Tuesday and Thursday.
